DIGEST
SB 81 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Morris
Present law provides that a defendant in a noncapital case may knowingly, intelligently,
irrevocably, and unilaterally waive his right to a jury trial up to 45 days prior to the
commencement of trial. Present law further provides that he may, with the consent of the
district attorney, waive his right to a jury trial within 45 days of the commencement of trial.
Proposed law provides that a defendant in a noncapital case may waive his right to a jury
trial at any time prior to the commencement of trial with the written consent of the
prosecuting authority.
Proposed law otherwise retains present law.
Effective only if the proposed amendment to La. Const. Art. I, Sec. 17(A) which originated
as Senate Bill No. 97 of the 2026 Regular Session is adopted at a statewide election and
becomes effective.
(Amends C.Cr.P. Art. 780(C))
